I have a doubt that what is the need of bubble sort as both selection and bubble have the same time complexity and they perform the same operation any answer to this ??

Bubble sort complexity - 
Time complexity - 
1. Best case - O(n) ( if array is already sorted )
2. Average case - O(n^2)
3. Worst case - O(n^2)

Space complexity - O(the number of extra variables used) if 1 extra variable  then O(1) , if 2 extra variable then O(2).

Following are the Time and Space complexity for the Bubble Sort algorithm.

Worst Case Time Complexity [ Big-O ]: O(n2)
Best Case Time Complexity [Big-omega]: O(n)
Average Time Complexity [Big-theta]: O(n2)
Space Complexity: O(1)
